Kurt Lidell Schmoke (born December 1, 1949) is an American politician and lawyer who served as the 46th mayor of Baltimore, Maryland, the first African American to be elected mayor. He is the current president of the University of Baltimore (UB), and former Dean of the Howard University School of Law.



Contents


1 Early years
2 High school
3 College and graduate school
4 Early career
5 Elective office
6 Advocacy for school choice and school vouchers
7 Life after politics
