Insider Activity


Individual




Kurt L. Schmoke



Mr. Kurt L. Schmoke is President at University of Baltimore, Independent Director at McGraw Hill Financial, Inc., Vice President & General Counsel at Howard University, Independent Director at Legg Mason, Inc., Chairman at Howard Hughes Medical Institute, Inc., and a Member at Council on Foreign Relations, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at Baltimore Development Corp., McGraw Hill Financial, Inc., and Legg Mason, Inc.
Mr. Schmoke was previously employed as Partner by Wilmer Cutler & Pickering and President by Jimmy Carter Library & Museum. He also served on the board at Foundation for the National Institutes of Health, Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from Yale University and a graduate degree from Harvard Law School.



